[SN]TITLE[SN]
Nottingham Open: Denis Istomin beats Sam Querrey in final

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Uzbekistan's Denis Istomin beat Sam Querrey 7-6 (7-1) 7-6 (8-6) to win his first ATP title at the Aegon Open.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Istomin, 28, is ranked 92nd in the world, 48 places below the American 12th seed, and had lost four of the pair's last five meetings.
He led 5-2 in the second set, but dropped two breaks before recovering on the tie-break to seal victory two days before the start of Wimbledon.
Querrey, 27, had been looking for a first title since 2012 in Nottingham.
Earlier on Centre Court, Chris Guccione and Andre Sa beat Pablo Cuevas and David Marrero 6-2 7-5 in the doubles final.
